Name: Joseph I. Lieberman

Name: Joseph I. Lieberman

Speech: If you don't stop it in six months, we'll ask the Federal Trade Commission to take action against you.

Text: I repeat it today.
Speech: I repeat it today.
Speaker: LIEBERMAN
Name: Joseph I. Lieberman

Text: We won't stop until the entertainment industry stops marketing its products to our children.

Text: LIEBERMAN: Al Gore and I agree on most everything, but we disagree on some things.

Name: Joseph I. Lieberman

Text: But he said to me, be yourself, thatâ€™s why I chose you, don't change a single position you have.

Speech: And I have not changed a single position since Al Gore nominated me to be his vice president.

Name: Joseph I. Lieberman

Text: LIEBERMAN: That went very quickly.

Name: Joseph I. Lieberman

Text: Thank you, Bernie, and thanks, Dick Cheney, for a very good debate.
Speech: Thank you, Bernie, and thanks, Dick Cheney, for a very good debate.
Speaker: LIEBERMAN
Name: Joseph I. Lieberman

Text: I'm told tens of millions of people have been watching this debate tonight.
Speech: I'm told tens of millions of people have been watching this debate tonight.

Name: Joseph I. Lieberman

Text: I must say, I wish one more person were here to watch and that is my dad, who died 15 years ago.

Speaker: LIEBERMAN
Name: Joseph I. Lieberman

Text: If my dad were here, I would have the opportunity to tell him that he was right when he taught me that in America, if you have faith, work hard and play by the rules, there is nothing you cannot achieve.
Speech: If my dad were here, I would have the opportunity to tell him that he was right when he taught me that in America, if you have faith, work hard and play by the rules, there is nothing you cannot achieve.
Speaker: LIEBERMAN
Name: Joseph I. Lieberman

Text: And here I am even the son of a man who started working the night shift on a bakery truck can end up being a candidate for Vice President of the United States.
Speech: And here I am even the son of a man who started working the night shift on a bakery truck can end up being a candidate for Vice President of the United States.
Speaker: LIEBERMAN
Name: Joseph I. Lieberman

Text: That says a lot about the character of this nation and the goodness of you, the American people.
Speech: That says a lot about the character of this nation and the goodness of you, the American people.
Speaker: LIEBERMAN
Name: Joseph I. Lieberman

Text: I will tell you that Hadassah and I have traveled around this country in the last couple of months and met thousands and thousands of parents just like our moms and dads, hard working middle-class people paying their taxes, doing the jobs to keep the country running.
Speech: I will tell you that Hadassah and I have traveled around this country in the last couple of months and met thousands and thousands of parents just like our moms and dads, hard working middle-class people paying their taxes, doing the jobs to keep the country running.
Speaker: LIEBERMAN
Name: Joseph I. Lieberman

Text: Trying so hard to teach their kids right from wrong and believing in their hearts that their kids can make it.
Speech: Trying so hard to teach their kids right from wrong and believing in their hearts that their kids can make it.
Speaker: LIEBERMAN
Name: Joseph I. Lieberman

Text: I agree with them.
Speech: I agree with them.
Speaker: LIEBERMAN
Name: Joseph I. Lieberman

Text: But to make it they need a leader who will stand up and fight for them for good education, the best education in the world.
Speech: But to make it they need a leader who will stand up and fight for them for good education, the best education in the world.
Speaker: LIEBERMAN
Name: Joseph I. Lieberman

Text: For a sound retirement system, for prescription drug benefits for their parents.

Name: Joseph I. Lieberman

Name: Joseph I. Lieberman

Speaker: LIEBERMAN
Name: Joseph I. Lieberman

Speech: Now is not the time to settle for less than we can be.
Speaker: LIEBERMAN
Name: Joseph I. Lieberman

Text: CHENEY: Bernie, I want to thank you and Joe as well.
Speech: Bernie, I want to thank you and Joe as well.
Speaker: CHENEY
Name: Richard(Dick) B. Cheney

Text: I've enjoyed the debate this evening.
Speech: I've enjoyed the debate this evening.
Speaker: CHENEY
Name: Richard(Dick) B. Cheney

Text: And thank the folks here at the Centre College in Danville, Kentucky, theyâ€™ve done a tremendous job of making this possible.
Speech: And thank the folks here at the Centre College in Danville, Kentucky, theyâ€™ve done a tremendous job of making this possible.
Speaker: CHENEY
Name: Richard(Dick) B. Cheney

Text: This is a very important decision you're going to make on November 7.
Speech: This is a very important decision you're going to make on November 7.
Speaker: CHENEY
Name: Richard(Dick) B. Cheney

Text: We have a fundamental choice between whether or not we continue with our old ways of big government, high taxes and ever more intrusive bureaucracy, or whether we take a new course for a new era.
Speech: We have a fundamental choice between whether or not we continue with our old ways of big government, high taxes and ever more intrusive bureaucracy, or whether we take a new course for a new era.
Speaker: CHENEY
Name: Richard(Dick) B. Cheney

Text: Governor Bush and I want to pursue the new course.
Speech: Governor Bush and I want to pursue the new course.
Speaker: CHENEY
Name: Richard(Dick) B. Cheney

Text: We want to reform the Social Security system to guarantee benefits will be there for our retired folks, as well as make it possible for our young people to invest a portion of their payroll tax into a retirement account that they'll control and give them greater control over their own lives.
Speech: We want to reform the Social Security system to guarantee benefits will be there for our retired folks, as well as make it possible for our young people to invest a portion of their payroll tax into a retirement account that they'll control and give them greater control over their own lives.
Speaker: CHENEY
Name: Richard(Dick) B. Cheney

Text: We want to reform the Medicare system to make certain the benefits are there for our senior citizens, but also to provide prescription drug coverage for them and give them a range of choices in terms of the kind of insurance we have.
Speech: We want to reform the Medicare system to make certain the benefits are there for our senior citizens, but also to provide prescription drug coverage for them and give them a range of choices in terms of the kind of insurance we have.
Speaker: CHENEY
Name: Richard(Dick) B. Cheney

Text: We want to reform the education system.
Speech: We want to reform the education system.

Name: Richard(Dick) B. Cheney

Text: We want to restore our public schools to the greatness they once represented so that every parent has the opportunity to choose what is best for their child and so that every child has an opportunity to share in the American dream.
Speech: We want to restore our public schools to the greatness they once represented so that every parent has the opportunity to choose what is best for their child and so that every child has an opportunity to share in the American dream.
Speaker: CHENEY
Name: Richard(Dick) B. Cheney

Text: We also want to reform the tax code.
Speech: We also want to reform the tax code.
Speaker: CHENEY
Name: Richard(Dick) B. Cheney

Text: We think it's very important now that we have a surplus, that a portion of that surplus go back to the people who earned it.
Speech: We think it's very important now that we have a surplus, that a portion of that surplus go back to the people who earned it.

Name: Richard(Dick) B. Cheney

Name: Richard(Dick) B. Cheney

Text: You're entitled to it, and we would like to see to it that we provide tax relief for everybody who pays taxes.
